South Africa’s Gasoline Price to Drop 0.2% After Oil-Products Costs Slide

-- B y   N a s r e e n   S e r i a
-- 
2011-05-27T10:51:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-27/south-africa-s-gasoline-price-to-drop-0-2-after-oil-products-costs-slide.html
South Africa ’s gasoline price to
decline 0.2 percent on June 1 after international oil-product
costs decreased, the Department of Energy said.  Gasoline will drop 2 cents a liter to 10.23 rand in Gauteng
province, the Pretoria-based department said in an e-mailed
statement. Diesel will fall as much as 38 cents a liter, while
kerosene will decline as much as 42 cents, the statement said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nasreen Seria at 
 nseria@bloomberg.net  